history.text: Hi! I just watched "Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice" and I have to say it's my favorite super hero movie from 2016! Have you seen it>
yes i have
i thought it was great
yes i saw it
I loved Henry Cavil's performance as Superman. I really believe that he had those powers! Who was your favorite character?
i realy enjoyed batman
Batman was a great character. His story arc was probably the strongest in my opinion.
overall did you like the movie?
Yes I really loved the movie and everything about it! It's one of my favorites.
did you have a favorite scene ?
I think I really enjoyed seeing how Batman and Superman interacted. What about you?
i agree with you i enjoyed when they met up for the first time

do you usually enjoy 
dc

 to see!
*dc comic movies ?
I'm not really into comics themselves but I love these super hero comic book movies. They really get my attention and keep me excitied.
would you like to see more movies where two super heros team up ?
I suppose so. I haven't tended to be into those sort of team movies or versus movies. But if I like the characters I don't see any reason that I would avoid the movies.
did you see the movie in a theater or somewhere else?
I saw it in theaters. Those sort of action movies are always best on big screens.
yes i agree
did you only watch it once?
Yes. I only watch movies one time. I very rarely repeat movies multiple times.
how did you like the villians in the movie?

They were unique and strong characters. I felt their emotions and did acually feel bad for t
hem.
i agree with you
was there anything you didnt like about the movie?

Not really the whole movie was really well done and put together in a very succulent
 manner. I could barley take my eyes off the screen.
did you think the movie was too long?
No not at all. I know the actual length is over two hours but it hardly felt that way when I was watching it. I honestly felt like I had just sat down and then the credits started.
would you want to see a sequel to this movi with both batman and superman in it?
I think that would be an interesting sequel. I loved seeing how the two of them worked together and figure that could be improved.
